def example_ml_copilot_ws():
            client = KittyCAD()  # Uses KITTYCAD_API_TOKEN environment variable

            # Connect to the websocket.
            with client.ml.ml_copilot_ws(conversation_id=None,
        replay=None) as websocket:

                # Send a message.

),

line=10,
),
),
)],
)))

                # Get a message.
                message = websocket.recv()
                print(message)

def example_modeling_commands_ws():
            client = KittyCAD()  # Uses KITTYCAD_API_TOKEN environment variable

            # Connect to the websocket.
            with client.modeling.modeling_commands_ws(fps=10,
        post_effect=PostEffectType.PHOSPHOR,
        show_grid=False,
        unlocked_framerate=False,
        video_res_height=10,
        video_res_width=10,
        webrtc=False,
        api_call_id=None,
        pool=None,
        replay=None) as websocket:

                # Send a message.
                websocket.send(WebSocketRequest(OptionTrickleIce(

)))
